Closes https://github.com/blakadder/zigbee/issues/1251

---

This reworks the `tablerow.html` include file so that:
* Images aren't squished;
* Product names are slightly bigger;
* Model numbers are slightly smaller;
* Product names, model numbers and compatibility icons appear on top of each other, and…
* … images take up 3 rows so that they align with the product details;
* It can now be included everywhere by default and the compatibility icons get hidden if the `hide_compat` variable is present (⚠️ This means the `tablerow_nocompatibility.html` file should now be safe to delete. I didn't, but feel free to ask for it.)

This PR will also fix the non-scrolling mobile navigation.
And will also allow more vertical space for the affiliate disclaimer text in the navigation on large layouts — it was partially hidden.
Lastly, it replaces the non-existent HTML element `sidebar` with `nav` which represents a navigation.

@blakadder please take a look at this when you can and let me know if you would like some tweaking.

Hey @blakadder! I sent you an email sometime ago but never got a reply, so here I am.

First things first, thanks a lot for this list/repository! It's very useful, especially for new zigbee users like myself.
The issue I find with it though, is that I use it mostly on my phone, and as you can see below, the layout is broken:

![Image](https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/0c113130-27f9-4403-902c-653bfcd244a2)

![Image](https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/963b31d3-4543-4e32-95f1-a2c515167517)

These are the issues I could find:
1. The images look squished;
2. There's no way to see the compatibility icons without scrolling horizontally;
3. The product names need more horizontal space to be easily readable;
4. The menu doesn't scroll vertically to reveal all menu items;

Would you be willing to accept a PR where I try to fix them? Can't promise anything, especially since you're using tables and I'm not sure how comfortable you would be moving to another approach. But at least I would like to give this at try.

I just wouldn't like to spend time looking into this if you're not willing to change it in the first place.

